                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.93/1779</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<hi
                        rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>)<note n="50" xml:id="d578fn50">Addressed to
                        the Director and the Deputy Director of the Office of Far Eastern Affairs
                        (Grew and Ballantine).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-23">May 23,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In talking to me yesterday afternoon before preparing to leave to return to his
                    post, Ambassador Harriman said the President requested him to do the
                    following:</p>
                <p>Discuss with Molotov the Chinese situation, particularly Molotov’s, purported
                    complaints against the Chungking government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E[<hi rend="smallcaps">dward</hi>] S[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >tettinius</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
